<div style=position:absolute;top:21666;left:0><hr><table border=0 width=100%><tr><td bgcolor=eeeeee align=right><font face=arial,sans-serif><a name=19><b>Page 19</b></a></font></td></tr></table></div><font size=3 color=#231f20 face=Times><span style=font-size:12px;font-family:Times;color:#231f20>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21779;left:49><nobr>of public sector PPP teams. The major knowledge gaps con-</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21797;left:49><nobr>sidered in PPP projects are areas concerning with financial risk</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21815;left:49><nobr>allocation, public involvement, consultant management, and</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21833;left:49><nobr>information imbalances (<a href=#20></a><font color=#2e3192><a href=#20>Boyer, 2016</a></font><a href=#20></a>). An exploration of what</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21850;left:49><nobr>kind of knowledge management approach can contribute towards</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21868;left:49><nobr>filling these knowledge gaps should be explored in the future.</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21886;left:49><nobr>Consequently, this would improve the capacity of public sector</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21904;left:49><nobr>for developing PPPs.</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21922;left:67><nobr>Although publications metrics in the form of citation counts</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21940;left:49><nobr>and measures of impact have long been used as indicators for</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21958;left:49><nobr>knowledge creation and research output, systematic knowledge</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21976;left:49><nobr>management research is still inadequate. A considerable amount</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21994;left:49><nobr>of research has shown the importance of knowledge manage-</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22012;left:49><nobr>ment (<a href=#22></a><font color=#2e3192><a href=#22>Nissen et al., 2014</a></font>; <font color=#2e3192><a href=#22>Tahat, 2014</a></font>), but research on how to</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22030;left:49><nobr>manage knowledge and fill the apparent knowledge gaps in PPP</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22048;left:49><nobr>projects remains relatively underdeveloped. It is suggested</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22066;left:49><nobr>that additional studies should be carried out to apply and</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22084;left:49><nobr>develop methods to enhance knowledge management such</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22101;left:49><nobr>as knowledge sharing, knowledge spillover, and knowledge</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22119;left:49><nobr>ontology building.</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22137;left:67><nobr>PPP projects are very information-intensive, partially due to</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22155;left:49><nobr>a large number of stakeholders from different disciplines.</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22173;left:49><nobr>Several processes must be completed simultaneously within</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22191;left:49><nobr>strict timelines, and a plethora of documents must be generated</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22209;left:49><nobr>by different software or systems across every PPP project. In</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22227;left:49><nobr>response to deficiencies in knowledge management methods</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22245;left:49><nobr>for PPP projects, we suggest the following the solutions. First,</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22263;left:49><nobr>effective information integration methods are very important</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22281;left:49><nobr>to achieve high-efficiency PPP project management, and hence</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22299;left:49><nobr>should be studied in the future. Second, more studies on the</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22317;left:49><nobr>application and development of knowledge management</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22335;left:49><nobr>methods, including knowledge sharing and knowledge spill-</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22353;left:49><nobr>over, must be conducted. Third, scholars should turn their</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22370;left:49><nobr>attention to the study of knowledge ontology building and its</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22388;left:49><nobr>application.</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22425;left:49><nobr><b>7. Conclusions</b></nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22460;left:67><nobr>Due to the growing interest in the research and application</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22478;left:49><nobr>of PPP procurement, this study presented a detailed review of</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22496;left:49><nobr>the status quo, gaps, and research suggestion for the future of</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22514;left:49><nobr>PPP research for infrastructure projects. The main contributions</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22532;left:49><nobr>of this study are fourfold. First, the overview of PPP researches</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22550;left:49><nobr>is based on the title of the study, publication year, journal title,</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22568;left:49><nobr>country or region where the studies are conducted, project</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22586;left:49><nobr>types, disciplines of the screened studies, and selection of the</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22604;left:49><nobr>research articles. Theoretical foundations of PPP research in</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22622;left:49><nobr>disciplines is set up to analyse the main theoretical foundations</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22640;left:49><nobr>and special theories. Second, unlike most preceding literature</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22657;left:49><nobr>reviews, this review is guided by a systematic process. It</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22675;left:49><nobr>combines a three-phase word frequency analysis, cluster</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22693;left:49><nobr>analysis, and an assessment of potential research topics. This</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22711;left:49><nobr>process helps to summarise the appropriate topics related to</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22729;left:49><nobr>PPP and to overcome some of the arbitrariness and subjectivity</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22747;left:49><nobr>involved in research topic analysis. The word frequency and</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22765;left:49><nobr>cluster analyses, which have a higher degree of similarity on the</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22783;left:49><nobr>basis of the occurrence and frequency of words, are clustered</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21779;left:453><nobr>and used to explore the status quo and research topic more</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21797;left:453><nobr>quantitatively. Third, six research topics are explored, including</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21815;left:453><nobr>financial package and PPP application, economic viability</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21833;left:453><nobr>and VFM, risk management and success factor, procurement</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21850;left:453><nobr>and contract management, performance management, and</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21868;left:453><nobr>governance and regulation. In addition, relationship between</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21886;left:453><nobr>different research groups is analysed, based on the theoretical</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21904;left:453><nobr>foundations framework. Fourth, a research gaps framework is</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21922;left:453><nobr>set up, based on research topics and the theoretical foundations</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21940;left:453><nobr>of PPP research. On this basis, several research gaps are</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21958;left:453><nobr>identified and research directions are provided. The methods</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21976;left:453><nobr>for conducting word frequency and cluster analyses together</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:21994;left:453><nobr>with the process of research gaps identification, based on the</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22012;left:453><nobr>systematic theoretical analysis, reduce subjective judgment in</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22030;left:453><nobr>current research effectively. The findings can provide some</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22048;left:453><nobr>conclusions on the status quo of PPP research and guide</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22066;left:453><nobr>researchers in selecting the research topic in the future.</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22084;left:470><nobr>Although the current study contributes to the literature on</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22101;left:453><nobr>PPP infrastructure projects research by summarising research</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22119;left:453><nobr>topics and exploring research gaps, it also has some limitations</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22137;left:453><nobr>that need to be addressed by conducting further research. First,</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22155;left:453><nobr>there are undoubtedly other PPP types being practiced in PPP</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22173;left:453><nobr>infrastructure projects, such as BOO, BOOT, and ROT. Second,</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22191;left:453><nobr>although literature that include ‘infrastructure’ in the full text</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22209;left:453><nobr>were searched, some studies on PPP infrastructure projects are</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22227;left:453><nobr>not included in the study because the word ‘infrastructure’ did</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22245;left:453><nobr>not appear in the study.</nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22291;left:453><nobr><b>Con</b>fl<b>ict of interest</b></nobr></div>
<div style=position:absolute;top:22327;left:470><nobr>There is no conflict of interest for this research paper.</nobr></div>
